description:

name: Print please - unique screenprints
description:
Three different patterns screenprinted by hand to a high quality paper. All numbered and signed; only ten each printed. So definitely a unique piece to decorate your wall with. 

You can choose from three different patterns and with or without a frame. The prints are A3, as in 30 cm x 42 cm. The frames are black, and a few centimeters bigger than the actual print. 

Patterns are
Up there; the print with a curious reindeer looking up,
Best friend; the one with neon pink diamonds falling and
Dreamcatcher on it's all simplicity.

name: Red diamonds -xmas cards
description:
Diamonds fit to any occasion, right? So send your xmas wishes this year with these beautiful hand printed cards.

Cards are screenprinted by hand to high quality 230g/m2 art paper. One card is 10,5 cm x 14 cm. The back side is empty, except the company logo on the left down corner.

It's highly recommended to send these with envelopes, the ink and the paper will have an affect on any moist contact.

name: Monkey business -xmas cards
description:
Monkeys to make your xmas wishes? Why not?

Set of four different monkeys and four different wishes;
Yellow and the monkey choir with "Rauhallista joulua",
Red and the waving monkey with "Iloista joulua",
Green and the gift giving monkey with "Hyvää joulua" and
Blue and the monkey riding a reindeer with "Hauskaa joulua".

All originals were hand drawn/painted with pastel chalk and aquarels, then printed on to 250g/m2 high quality paper. One card is 10 cm x 13,5 cm. The back side includes address lines and a space for your wishes. Can be send without an envelope.

You can choose a set with all four, or select your own combination one by one. 

Don't want to use papercards? Download and send our free e-cards from bit.ly/1ehft4x

name: Xmas -gift wrap
description:
The prettier the package, happier the receiver. So this xmas you can decorate your gifts with these unique, hand printed wrapping papers!

Two patterns available; 
'Up there' with the cute reindeer and
'Diamonds' with some red goodness.

Papers are sold in sheets size 36 cm x 52 cm. The paper is 90g/m2 litoposter.

name: Check/Mate -mittens
description:
It's getting cold, so better prepare! 

This design was originally made by my mom, she's been knitting mittens like these as long as I remember. And 'cos they've been loved so much, why not share the love for you too?

Five color combinations available;
First crush: light grey w/ multipastel,
First snow: white w/ multipastel,
Sundown: light grey w/pink,
Midnite: dark grey w/ green, petrol and purple and
Suomi: blue w/ white.

Two sizes available, normal (s-m) and large (l-xl).

Handknitted, 75% wool + 25% acryl.
Machine wash cold.

name: Xmas -pendant
description:

The bottle is 4cm tall and it comes with nickel free approx. 80cm long chain. 

Part of the 'Bottled' -jewellery collection. The bottles and caps are recycled, and the insides are recycled/surplus.

Part of the 'Bottled' -jewellery collection. The bottles and caps are recycled, and the insides are recycled/surplus.

Evening: dark grey w/ green,
Miami surf: turqoise w/ multipastel,

I, myself have like 15 different color combinations at my closet, which is your favorite?

This beanie keeps you happy and warm for the whole year round.

Happy was originally a custom job for this one guy that I was attracted to during university. After giving it to him, he was frequently asked about the beanie, so I made it part of the permanent collection. And the story goes on and now, we live happily together. Maybe this will bring some good luck to you too?

One size. 

75% wool, 25% polyamide.

I've drawn this print actually four years ago, and now it finally made into a fabric and into a hoodie, as I then imagined. And how cool of a hoodie it became? Huh.

Two colors available. Sizes are marked by womens standards, but M size fits S-size men, L M-size men and so on.

Does the print look familiar? This print was also part of Helsinki Design Week 2010, when it was taped to a metro cart and projected into Kamppi metrostation ceiling.

name: Gamer -hoodie
description:
As you all might have noticed, I am a old school gamer with 8-bit Nintendos and shit. So I got inspired to draw this print from old Zelda -games. My 'not so old school' friends keep buggin' me, that there isn't no lifeforce heart's with one third missing. At least at their memories, which seem not to be so oldschool.

Two colors available; dark grey and green. 
M size fits S-size men as well.

name: Third heart -tank top
description:
Again with the Lifeforce -print, but not gamer-like. This tank top is loose on sizing, so it's very comfy and at the same time stylish.

At the moment only white available, more colors coming closer to fall.

name: Tribal -tank
description:
I came up with this print just doodling around on some quiet days at my last part time job. I suddenly enjoy these kind of almost graphic designs, but still with lively lines. 

This tank top is loose fit, so it's comfy and cool at the same time. At the left side there's a actual small pocket for your valuables.

Two colors available, more coming before xmas.

description:
This print got started as a doole on my notebook. Graphic but lively lines with just few colors are kind of a new thing to me and my print designs, but it inspires me a lot. 

This tee is perfect for all you little hipsters out there. Although Joni likes this a lot, and he is a engineer. So maybe it suits not all but many. 

Men's sizes, but who says that ladies couldn't wear this as well?

Dreamcathers are so inspiring and so IN at the moment as well.

I wanted to take a different aesthetic approach on prints a while back. A different from what people had learnt to know me about. So, I got lured in to a ethereal place with dreamcatchers and feathers. This print is what came of that.

These tees are unique, 'cos each and everyone are hand dyed and hand printed.
